	<artifactId>service-registry</artifactId>
	<version>0.0.1-SNAPSHOT</version>
	<name>service-registry</name>
	<description>Service Registry for Product-Order Microservices,
	 This project implements a Service Registry for a Spring Bootâ€“based microservices
	 architecture using Netflix Eureka.
	 The Service Registry acts as a central directory where 
	 all microservices register themselves and discover
	 other services dynamically without hard-coded URLs.
  In a microservices environment where services are frequently scaled up/down 
  and deployed on different hosts, the Service Registry ensures loose coupling,
  scalability, and fault tolerance by enabling dynamic service discovery.
  </description>
